Package main.java.de.bsi.seapi.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ErrorCertificateExpired
    This class defines the exception ErrorCertificateExpired that is thrown if a SE API function is invoked and the certificate with the public key for the verification of the appropriate type of log messages is expired.
    ErrorDeleteStoredDataFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorDeleteStoredDataFailed that is thrown if the deletion of the data from the storage failed
    ErrorDescriptionNotSetByManufacturer
    This class defines the exception ErrorDescriptionNotSetByManufacturer that is thrown if the function initialize has been invoked without a value for the input parameter description although the description of the SE API has not been set by the manufacturer
    ErrorDescriptionSetByManufacturer
    This class defines the exception ErrorDescriptionSetByManufacturer that is thrown if the function initialize has been invoked with a value for the input parameter description although the description of the SE API has been set by the manufacturer.
    ErrorDisableSecureElementFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorDisableSecureElementFailed that is thrown if the deactivation of the Secure Element failed
    ErrorExportCertFailed
    The exception ErrorExportCertFailed is thrown if the collection of the certificates for the export failed
    ErrorExportSerialNumbersFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorExportSerialNumbersFailed that is thrown if the collection of the serial number(s) failed
    ErrorFinishTransactionFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorFinishTransactionFailed that is thrown if the execution of the Secure Element functionality for finishing a transaction failed
    ErrorGetCurrentNumberOfClientsFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorGetCurrentNumberOfClientsFailed that is thrown if the determination of the current number of clients using the SE API failed
    ErrorGetCurrentNumberOfTransactionsFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorGetCurrentNumberOfTransactionsFailed that is thrown if the determination of the number of currently opened transactions failed
    ErrorGetMaxNumberOfClientsFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorGetMaxNumberOfClientsFailed that is thrown if the determination of the maximum number of clients that could use the SE API simultaneously failed
    ErrorGetMaxNumberTransactionsFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorGetMaxNumberTransactionsFailed that is thrown if the determination of the maximum number of transactions that can be managed simultaneously failed
    ErrorGetSupportedUpdateVariantsFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorGetSupportedUpdateVariantsFailed that is thrown if the identification of the supported variant(s) for updating transactions failed.
    ErrorGetTimeSyncVariantFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorGetTimeSyncVariantFailed that is thrown if the identification of the supported variant for updating the current date/time failed.
    ErrorIdNotFound
    This class defines the exception ErrorIdNotFound that is thrown if no data has been found for the provided clientID in the context of the export of stored data
    ErrorInvalidTime
    This class defines the exception ErrorInvalidTime that is thrown if the time transmitted parameters are not valid, e.g. year out of bounds
    ErrorNoDataAvailable
    This class defines the exception ErrorNoDataAvailable that is thrown if no data has been found for the provided selection in the context of the export of stored data
    ErrorNoLogMessage
    This class defines the exception ErrorNoLogMessage that is thrown if no log message parts have been found in the Secure Element
    ErrorNoTransaction
    This class defines the exception ErrorNoTransaction that is thrown if no transaction is known to be open under the provided transaction number
    ErrorParameterMismatch
    This class defines the exception ErrorParameterMismatch that is thrown if there is a mismatch regarding the particular parameters that have been provided in the context of the export of stored data
    ErrorReadingLogMessage
    This class defines the exception ErrorReadingLogMessage that is thrown if the retrieving of the log message parts that have been created from Secure Element most recently failed
    ErrorRestoreFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorRestoreFailed that is thrown if the restore process in the context of a restoring from a backup in form of exported data failed
    ErrorRetrieveLogMessageFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorRetrieveLogMessageFailed that is thrown if the retrieving of the log message parts that have been created by Secure Element most recently failed
    ErrorSeApiNotInitialized
    This class defines the exception ErrorSeApiNotInitialized that is thrown if a SE API function is invoked although the SE API has not been initialized
    ErrorSecureElementDisabled
    This class defines the exception ErrorSecureElementDisabled that is thrown if SE API functions are invoked although the Secure Element has been disabled
    ErrorSigningSystemOperationDataFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorSigningSystemOperationDataFailed that is thrown if the determination of the log message parts for the system operation data by the Secure Element failed
    ErrorStartTransactionFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorStartTransactionFailed that is thrown if the execution of the Secure Element functionality to start a transaction failed
    ErrorStorageFailure
    This class defines the exception ErrorStorageFailure that is thrown if storing of the log message in the storage failed
    ErrorStoringInitDataFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorStoringInitDataFailed that is thrown if the storing of the initialization data during the commissioning of the SE API by the application operator failed
    ErrorTimeNotSet
    This class defines the exception ErrorTimeNotSet that is thrown if an appropriate SE API function is invoked although the managed data/time in the Secure Element has not been updated after the initialization of the SE API or a period of absence of current for the Secure Element
    ErrorTooManyRecords
    This class defines the exception ErrorTooManyRecords that is thrown if the amount of requested records exceeds the passed value for the maximum number of records in the context of the export of stored data
    ErrorTransactionNumberNotFound
    This class defines the exception ErrorTransactionNumberNotFound that is thrown if no data has been found found for the provided transaction number(s) in the context of the export of stored data
    ErrorUnexportedStoredData
    This class defines the exception ErrorUnexportedStoredData that is thrown if deletion of data from the storage failed because the storage contains data that has not been exported
    ErrorUpdateTimeFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorUpdateTimeFailed that is thrown if the execution of the Secure Element functionality for setting the time failed
    ErrorUpdateTransactionFailed
    This class defines the exception ErrorUpdateTransactionFailed that is thrown if the execution of the Secure Element functionality for updating a transaction failed
    ErrorUserIdNotAuthenticated
    This class defines the exception ErrorUserIdNotAuthenticated that is thrown if the passed userId has not the status authenticated
    ErrorUserIdNotManaged
    This class defines the exception ErrorUserIdNotManaged that is thrown if the passed userId is not managed by the SE API
    ErrorUserNotAuthenticated
    This class defines the exception ErrorUserNotAuthenticated that is thrown if the user who has invoked a restricted SE API function has not the status "authenticated"
    ErrorUserNotAuthorized
    This class defines the exception ErrorUserNotAuthorized that is thrown if the user who has invoked a restricted SE API function is not authorized to execute this function
